2 CONC ; font-size: 18px; line-height: 23px; font-family: 'source sans pro', arial, sans-serif; color: #4a4a4a; background-color: #f8f8f8;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: border-box;"&gt;BILOTTI, Carolina (nee Mammoliti) - April 1910 to September 2008 Mot
2 CONC her we could find a thousand ways to say how wonderful you are but we don't need to say what's always in our hearts. Peacefully in her sleep our precious mother (nona) left us and has gone into the presence of Our Lord. Carolina will be remembere
2 CONC d with love and respect by her family, friends, and all whose lives she has touched over her 98 years of life. Her simplicity, faith and kind-hearted ways will never be forgotten. Loving wife for 65 years of the late &lt;strong&gt;Frank (1991)&lt;/
2 CONC strong&gt; and cherished mother of her &lt;strong&gt;late sons Valentino (Val 2007) and baby Franky.&lt;/strong&gt; Beloved mother and mother-in-law to Lucille (late Val) Bilotti, Louise (late Robert) Stevens, Norman Bilotti, Helen (late Clarence
2 CONC ) McCorkell, and Elizabeth (Michael) Giguere. Loving grandmother to Valerie (Des) Lever, Carolanne (Bill) Halkes, John McCorkell, Vanessa Giguere Michael Giguere, Earl (Irene) Price, Janet (Brian) Rumleski, Robin (Lynn) Price, Charlene Price, Frank
2 CONC y Price, Rosalie Bilotti, Jason Bilotti, Roxanne Bilotti, Annie Stevens, and Bobby Stevens. Great- Grandmother to 14 great-grandchildren and 4 great-great- grandchildren. &lt;strong&gt;Survived by one sister Yollie Paolini.&lt;/strong&gt; She wil
2 CONC l be missed by many nieces and nephews for whom she always had a soft spot in her heart. Predeceased by her sisters Ersilia (late Pete) Barratto, Lena (late Gino) Parisini, and Mary Mammoliti and her brothers Joseph (late Francis) Mammoliti, Orland
2 CONC o (Peggy) Mammoliti, Guido Mammoliti, Louis (late Antoinnette) Mammoliti and George (late Mildred) Mammoliti. Mother will always be remembered for her love of cooking not only at home but at the Dante Club and MacIntyre Arena where she catered many
2 CONC , many weddings and stags. A mother leaves her mark in the world with the love she gives her family. Funeral service will be held on Monday September 15, 2008 at 11 a.m. at Sacred Heart Church. Interment will follow at Timmins Memorial Cemetery. Re
2 CONC membrance donations to the Sacred Heart Church Elevator Fund or to the Charity of your Choice would be greatly appreciated. The family will receive friends on Sunday from 2 to 6 p.m. at LESSARD- STEPHENS Funeral Home. (705)268-4488. Online donation
2 CONC s or condolences can be made at&amp;nbsp;www.lessardstephens.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</line><line>&lt;div style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #767676; margin: 20px 0px 0px; font-family: 'source sans pro', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; b
2 CONC ackground-color: #f8f8f8;"&gt;Published on&amp;nbsp;September 12, 2008&lt;/div&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
